ormation Region (OIIX), as Washington weighs a fresh round of military strikes and Pakistani and Qatari mediators race to revive stalled US-Iran talks.\\nThe Iranian Civil Aviation Authority issued a Notice to Airmen (NOTAM) — OIIX A1010/26 — on Friday, May 22, ordering the shutdown of all airports in the western part of the Tehran FIR, effective immediately and valid until May 25, the Gulf News reported.\\nOnly eight airports across the country remain operational, including Tehran's Mehrabad and Imam Khomeini International, alongside Isfahan, Shiraz, Yazd, Tabriz, Mashhad and Bandar Abbas. Even at these, flights are restricted to daylight hours from sunrise to sunset, and airlines must obtain fresh per-flight approval from the Civil Aviation Authority, according to the NOTAM.\\nFlight-tracking data shows commercial aircraft already rerouting away from western Iranian airspace, with multiple airlines avoiding the corridor entirely.\\nThe article describes the closure as connected to anticipated military action and stalled US-Iran talks, not weather. It states the new NOTAM formalizes the most extensive restrictions in weeks.\\n\\n[defendant] DX-5 Arab Times report describing temporary airport restrictions\\nSource: Arab Times\\nURL: https://www.arabtimesonline.com/news/iran-suspends-flight-permissions-restricts-western-airspace-access/\\nRetrieved: 2026-06-20T00:00:25Z\\nHeadline: Iran Suspends Flight Permissions, Restricts Western Airspace Access\\nPublication date shown: 23/05/2026\\nRelevant captured text:\\nTEHRAN, May 23: Iran's Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) has issued a Notice to Airmen (NOTAM) announcing the temporary closure of all airports in the western part of the Tehran Flight Information Region (OIIX), except for a limited number of airports that will operate only during daylight hours from sunrise to sunset.\\nAccording to the NOTAM, the restrictions came into effect on May 22 and will remain valid until May 25, 2026. Airports permitted to continue limited operations include OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG and OIAW.\\nThe authority also suspended all previously granted flight permissions, stating that all airlines and operators must obtain fresh approval from the Civil Aviation Authority before conducting civil IFR passenger flights to or over the affected airports.\\nThe move comes amid heightened regional tensions and ongoing security concerns affecting air traffic operations across Iranian airspace.\\n\\n[defendant] DX-S1 A1010/26 airport wording and exceptions\\nSource: Notamify OIIX NOTAM page\\nURL: https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/693f2d0f-54d3-433b-8128-49f5475ba269\\nRetrieved: 2026-06-19T23:59:00Z\\nTitle shown: All west Tehran FIR airports are closed except listed airports operating sunrise to sunset, with new CAA permission required for civil IFR passenger flights.\\nNOTAM identifier: A1010/26\\nCategory: AD Airport Operations\\nPeriod of applicability shown: UTC 2026-05-22 20:46 - 2026-05-25 08:30\\nInterpretation shown: All airports in the west part of Tehran FIR are closed except OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, and OIAW, which are operational from sunrise to sunset. All previous permissions are suspended for all operators, and new permission must be requested from the CAA for operation of civil IFR passenger flights on these airports.\\nRaw NOTAM shown:\\nA1010/26 NOTAMR A0799/26\\nQ)OIIX/QFALC/IV/NBO/A/000/999/\\nA)OIIX B)2605222046 C)2605250830EST\\nE)REF NOTAM  A0796/26, ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART\\nOF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD\\nEXCEPT OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, AND OIAW THAT ARE\\nOPERATIONAL FM SUNRISE TO SUNSET (HJ).\\nALL PREVIOUS PERMISSIONS ARE SUSPENDED FOR ALL OPERATORS,\\nNEW PERMISSION SHALL BE REQUESTED FM CAA FOR OPRATION OF\\nCIVIL IFR PASSENGER FLIGHTS ON THESE AIRPORTS.\\nPage status text included: NOTAM Inactive.\\n\\n[defendant] DX-S2 A1015/26 expanded operational exceptions\\nSource: Notamify OIIX NOTAM page\\nURL: https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/6