orts across the country remain operational, including Tehran's Mehrabad and Imam Khomeini International, alongside Isfahan, Shiraz, Yazd, Tabriz, Mashhad and Bandar Abbas. Even at these, flights are restricted to daylight hours from sunrise to sunset, and airlines must obtain fresh per-flight approval from the Civil Aviation Authority, according to the NOTAM.\nFlight-tracking data shows commercial aircraft already rerouting away from western Iranian airspace, with multiple airlines avoiding the corridor entirely.\nThe article describes the closure as connected to anticipated military action and stalled US-Iran talks, not weather. It states the new NOTAM formalizes the most extensive restrictions in weeks.\n\n[defendant] DX-S4 Market rule requiring broad/general closure\n# Market page record\n\nOfficial event URL: https://polymarket.com/event/iran-closes-its-airspace-by\nOfficial May 24 market URL: https://polymarket.com/event/iran-closes-its-airspace-by/iran-closes-its-airspace-by-may-24\nCaptured API file: source-captures/polymarket-gamma-event.json\nCaptured May 24 API file: source-captures/polymarket-gamma-market-may-24.json\nCaptured event page file: source-captures/polymarket-page-and-api-extract.txt\nCaptured May 24 page file or error: source-captures/polymarket-gamma-market-may-24.json\nCapture time: 2026-05-24T01:44:04Z\n\n## Event\n\n- event id: 438327\n- ticker/slug: iran-closes-its-airspace-by / iran-closes-its-airspace-by\n- title: Iran closes its airspace by...?\n- event createdAt: 2026-05-01T16:11:36.585944Z\n- event creationDate: 2026-05-01T18:22:49.431549Z\n- event startDate: 2026-05-01T18:22:49.431559Z\n- event endDate: 2026-05-31T00:00:00Z\n- event active: True\n- event closed: False\n- event volume at capture: 34658537.51144401\n\n## May 24 market\n\n- market id: 2241873\n- slug: iran-closes-its-airspace-by-may-24\n- question: Iran closes its airspace by May 24?\n- groupItemTitle: May 24\n- conditionId: 0x4ba348328e4d4ddee9e6734c9a369b2e8138611651f9f6dc8f59dea51df6c734\n- questionID: 0x30ebd10971cc044380ce6495e791828e9e0291fbb48550ca8be42149e1982791\n- createdAt: 2026-05-12T15:03:45.641355Z\n- startDate: 2026-05-12T15:08:30.267422Z\n- endDate: 2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\n- endDateIso: 2026-05-24\n- active: True\n- closed: False\n- acceptingOrders: True\n- umaResolutionStatus: disputed\n- umaResolutionStatuses: [\"proposed\", \"disputed\", \"proposed\", \"disputed\"]\n- outcomes: [\"Yes\", \"No\"]\n- outcomePrices: [\"0.157\", \"0.843\"]\n- lastTradePrice: 0.16\n- bestBid/bestAsk: 0.15 / 0.164\n- updatedAt: 2026-05-24T01:35:13.748834Z\n- volume at capture: 8289170.735521075\n\n## Rule text\n\nThis market will resolve to “Yes” if Iran initiates a major closure of its airspace, that is not solely due to weather conditions, by the listed date, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to “No”.\n\nA “major closure” is defined as a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian Airspace region. A qualifying closure must apply generally to flights across Iran or a major Iranian airspace region. Limited cancellations, delays, or other partial closures will not qualify. Limited exceptions to a broad closure, however, will not disqualify such a closure from counting (e.g. exceptions for certain flights pre-approved by the Iranian Civil Aviation Authority may be permitted).\n\nAny non-weather complete suspension of commercial arrivals and departures affecting at least two of the following airports will qualify: Imam Khomeini International Airport (IKA), Mehrabad Airport (THR), Mashhad International Airport (MHD), Shiraz International Airport (SYZ), or Isfahan International Airport (IFN).\n\nQualifying previous examples include the January 2026 total closure of Iranian airspace except to international flights with express governmental permission (https://www.reuters.com/world/middle-east/iran-shuts-airspace-most-flights-flightradar24-says-2026-01-14/) and the April 2024 closure of Iran’s western airspace (https://www.reuters.com/world/middle-east/iranian-airports-cancel-flights-until-monday-morning-2024-04-14/). Non-qualifying examples include the January 27, 2026 partial closure of Iranian airspace around the Strait of Hormuz (https://www.aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iran-issues-airspace-notice-for-military-drills-near-strait-of-hormuz/3812508) and the January 25 - April 25, 2026 VFR (Visual Flight Rules) flights suspension which did not broadly close commercial aviation in a qualifying region (https://www.intellinews.com/iran-suspends-general-aviation-and-vfr-flights-in-new-airspace-directive-421997/).\n\nWarnings, No-Fly-Zones, or other flight restrictions imposed by airlines or countries other than Iran will not be sufficient for a “Yes” resolution.\n\nAirspace closures which occur solely due to weather conditions will not qualify.\n\nThe primary resolution sources for this market will be official information from Iranian aviation authorities and a consensus of credible reporting.\n\n## Notes for arbitration\n\nThe proposition tracks the rule text, not the platform-resolution question. The operative elements are: (1) Iran initiated the closure; (2) the closure was not solely weather-related; (3) the closure occurred by May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET; (4) the closure was a major closure, defined by the rule as a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region; or a non-weather complete suspension of commercial arrivals and departures affecting at least two listed airports; and (5) the primary sources are official information from Iranian aviation authorities and a consensus of credible reporting.\n\n\nSubmitted evidence:\n[plaintiff arguments] Notamify capture of OIIX A1010/26 raw NOTAM (ev_a95b8d7e6e97_submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-a95b8d7e6e97)\nSource: https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/693f2d0f-54d3-433b-8128-49f5475ba269\nSHA-256: `a95b8d7e6e97fa3e3ce64d2dbd0386a2e9cd33cc24d601a9d0a01f396d661025`\nBytes: 1286\nRelevance: Primary-like NOTAM text for Iran/Tehran FIR airport closure effective May 22-May 25, 2026; proves scope, timing, exceptions, CAA permission requirement, and non-weather aviation restriction source chain.\n\n[plaintiff arguments] Notamify capture of OIIX A1015/26 superseding NOTAM (ev_ecbf01d69176_submitted-evidence-02-plaintiff-ecbf01d69176)\nSource: https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/67435351-52f9-4d17-8f4c-497a21dd94bf\nSHA-256: `ecbf01d69176ce74c29122ea30dcf33188fcb3525efdf32b34308bf7f99c9552`\nBytes: 1238\nRelevance: Shows the closure remained in force past the May 24 ET deadline after A1015/26 replaced A1010/26, with expanded exception list and continued CAA permission requirement.\n\n[plaintiff arguments] Indian Express May 23 report on Iran western airspace closure (ev_a6be31686c80_submitted-evidence-03-plaintiff-a6be31686c80)\nSource: https://indianexpress.com/article/world/us-news/iran-closes-airspace-trump-cancels-plans-us-military-strikes-rubio-india-10704692/\nSHA-256: `a6be31686c80176d9d7195f76281647eb9a9d9b39b77a59b0b8e3d3ddbf8afa6`\nBytes: 1759\nRelevance: Credible reporting corroborating the NOTAM, CAA attribution, affected airports including listed market airports, operational limits, timing, and non-weather/security context.\n\n[plaintiff arguments] Arab Times May 23 report on Iran CAA western Tehran FIR restrictions (ev_098dc1dc0d2d_submitted-evidence-04-plaintiff-098dc1dc0d2d)\nSource: https://www.arabtimesonline.com/news/iran-suspends-flight-permissions-restricts-western-airspace-access/\nSHA-256: `098dc1dc0d2db3d30476992b3689d9a3ec6bcfb67085da015bc7ab644ebb85d4`\nBytes: 1224\nRelevance: Corroborates Iranian CAA attribution, May 22-May 25 timing, limited airport exceptions, suspension of prior permissions, fresh approval requirement, and security/non-weather context.\n\nTechnical reports:\n[plaintiff] Evidence search and weight ledger\nSearches targeted OIIX A1010/26, A1015/26, Iranian CAA attribution, May 22-May 25 timing, and adverse partial-closure issues. Direct official CAA custody was not captured; the strongest preserved source is raw NOTAM text from Notamify, corroborated by Indian Express and Arab Times reports. The airport lists in reporting are not perfectly identical to the raw NOTAM, so the plaintiff relies on the major-region closure path rather than the two-listed-airport complete-suspension path.\n\n[defendant] Defense Source And Scope Analysis\nRead all new plaintiff exhibits. The decisive source-chain problem is not timing or non-weather context but scope: the raw NOTAMs are third-party Notamify captures categorized as AD Airport Operations and focused on airport closures with many daylight operational exceptions and fresh CAA approvals. They do not directly prove a general suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, and the reports confirm continuing limited operations at several important airports.\n\nCall submit_council_vote with vote=demonstrated or vote=not_demonstrated.\nKeep the rationale brief: no more than three sentences.\n\nCouncil API instructions:\nYou are a council member. Decide the proposition from the admitted record.\nYou may examine admitted evidence through read-only tools when exact bytes, metadata, or exhibit contents matter.\nDo not search the web, introduce new facts, create new evidence, or upload evidence.\nWhen ready, call submit_council_vote exactly once with vote=demonstrated or vote=not_demonstrated and a concise rationale.\n","state":"ready","status":"ready","tools":[{"description":"Return the current visible arbitration record for this council member.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{},"type":"object"},"name":"get_case","read_only":true},{"description":"List visible immutable record evidence.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{},"type":"object"},"name":"list_evidence","read_only":true},{"description":"Return metadata and read limits for one visible evidence item.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{"evidence_id":{"type":"string"}},"required":["evidence_id"],"type":"object"},"name":"stat_evidence","read_only":true},{"description":"Read a bounded byte range from one visible evidence item as base64.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{"evidence_id":{"type":"string"},"length":{"minimum":1,"type":"integer"},"offset":{"minimum":0,"type":"integer"}},"required":["evidence_id","offset","length"],"type":"object"},"name":"read_evidence_range","read_only":true},{"description":"Submit one council vote for the current deliberation opportunity.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{"rationale":{"type":"string"},"vote":{"enum":["demonstrated","not_demonstrated"],"type":"string"}},"required":["vote","rationale"],"type":"object"},"name":"submit_council_vote","read_only":false}],"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":false,"deadline":"2026-06-20T00:24:37.848576192Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C4","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C4","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":885314,"role_id":"council","turn_number":12},"wait":{"reason":"ready","state_version":16,"version":25}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"wait_for_opportunity"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781914192540}]}
