perations across the western Tehran FIR, a major Iranian airspace region, with only limited CAA-controlled daylight exceptions, for non-weather reasons, effective through the deadline. This fits the major-region path.\n\nI'm ready to vote."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_015E4pR9TpQneE6Qj5tRoCYE","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted NOTAMs (A1010/26 and A1015/26) prove Iran's CAA closed ALL"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The admitted NOTAMs (A1010/26 and A1015/26) prove Iran's CAA closed ALL","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"anthropic/claude-opus-4.6-fast","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781914216015,"responseId":"gen-1781914216-MAWn8sj9Ssz0ChTPkjX0","responseModel":"anthropic/claude-4.6-opus-fast-20260407"}}
