ll","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260619235218\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 879123\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260619235218\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"content_base64\":\"\",\"evidence_id\":\"ev_e61df84283cc_market-page\",\"length\":4971,\"mime_type\":\"text/plain\",\"offset\":0,\"remaining_read_bytes_for_opportunity\":518031,\"remaining_reads_for_opportunity\":30,\"sha256\":\"e61df84283cc858bfd0cf8235c6f1d53a10d6e1c37b2d97256da8f1e6391cc17\",\"total_size_bytes\":4971},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":false,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-20T00:24:37.848576192Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":879123,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex11a-20260619235218","member_id":"C4","ok":true,"result":{"content_base64":"","evidence_id":"ev_e61df84283cc_market-page","length":4971,"mime_type":"text/plain","offset":0,"remaining_read_bytes_for_opportunity":518031,"remaining_reads_for_opportunity":30,"sha256":"e61df84283cc858bfd0cf8235c6f1d53a10d6e1c37b2d97256da8f1e6391cc17","total_size_bytes":4971},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":false,"deadline":"2026-06-20T00:24:37.848576192Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C4","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C4","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":879123,"role_id":"council","turn_number":12}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"read_evidence_range"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781914198726},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've now confirmed the raw evidence. Let me decode the key exhibits to verify their contents match the record."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01Jyb3zR9UmJ3haifMViktJQ","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"echo \"\" | base64 -d"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"anthropic/claude-opus-4.6-fast","usage":{"input":10276,"output":1629,"cacheRead":21738,"cacheWrite":2062,"totalTokens":35705,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781914198728,"responseId":"gen-1781914198-XofiGU98E7dgpQQj0i34","responseModel":"anthropic/claude-4.6-opus-fast-20260407"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01Jyb3zR9UmJ3haifMViktJQ","toolName":"bash","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Source: Notamify OIIX NOTAM page\nURL: https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/693f2d0f-54d3-433b-8128-49f5475ba269\nRetrieved: 2026-06-19T23:59:00Z\nTitle shown: All west Tehran FIR airports are closed except listed airports operating sunrise to sunset, with new CAA permission required for civil IFR passenger flights.\nNOTAM identifier: A1010/26\nCategory: AD Airport Operations\nPeriod of applicability shown: UTC 2026-05-22 20:46 - 2026-05-25 08:30\nInterpretation shown: All airports in the west part of Tehran FIR are closed except OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, and OIAW, which are operational from sunrise to sunset. All previous permissions are suspended for all operators, and new permission must be requested from the CAA for operation of civil IFR passenger flights on these airports.\nRaw NOTAM shown:\nA1010/26 NOTAMR A0799/26\nQ)OIIX/QFALC/IV/NBO/A/000/999/\nA)OIIX B)2605222046 C)2605250830EST\nE)REF NOTAM  A0796/26, ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART\nOF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD\nEXCEPT OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, AND OIAW THAT ARE\nOPERATIONAL FM SUNRISE TO SUNSET (HJ).\nALL PREVIOUS PERMISSIONS ARE SUSPENDED FOR ALL OPERATORS,\nNEW PERMISSION SHALL BE REQUESTED FM CAA FOR OPRATION OF\nCIVIL IFR PASSENGER FLIGHTS ON THESE AIRPORTS.\nPage status text included: NOTAM Inactive."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1781914216014},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, the raw evidence is confirmed. Now let me carefully analyze the key legal and factual questions before voting.\n\n**My analysis as C4:**\n\n**Uncontested elements:**\n1. **Iranian initiation**: Both sides agree. The NOTAM was issued by Iran's CAA (OIIX).\n2. **Non-weather**: Both sides agree. Security/military context, not weather.\n3. **Timing**: Both sides agree. A1010/26 began May 22, 20:46 UTC; A1015/26 ran through May 25, 08:30 UTC. The deadline was May 24, 11:59 PM ET = May 25, 03:59 UTC. The closure was in force at the deadline.\n\n**The contested element: Was this a \"major closure\"?**\n\nThe rule provides two qualifying paths:\n- **Path 1 (major-region)**: Broad closure/cancellation/suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region. Limited exceptions (including CAA pre-approved flights) don't disqualify.\n- **Path 2 (listed airports)**: Complete suspension of commercial arrivals/departures at ≥2 listed airports. Not pursued by plaintiff, and evidence shows listed airports had limited daylight operations.\n\n**Key considerations on Path 1:**\n\nThe NOTAM says \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD\" — this is a general closure with enumerated exceptions. The default is closed; specific airports are exempted only during daylight hours and only with fresh CAA permission. All prior permissions were suspended for all operators.\n\nThe defendant argues this is merely an \"airport operations\" restriction, not an airspace closure, and that the exceptions are too numerous to be \"limited.\" However:\n\n- The rule's own qualifying examples include \"the April 2024 closure of Iran's western airspace.\" The current event — closure of all airports in the west part of Tehran FIR — is structurally comparable to that qualifying example.\n- The rule explicitly contemplates that \"exceptions for certain flights pre-approved by the Iranian Civil Aviation Authority\" do not disqualify a broad closure. The NOTAM's permission regime is precisely this kind of exception.\n- \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD\" is a broad, region-wide measure. Closing all airports in a region effectively suspends commercial arrivals and departures across that region. The exceptions are enumerated, daylight-only, and require fresh individual CAA approval — these are exactly the \"limited exceptions\" the rule contemplates.\n- The Indian Express describes this as Iran closing \"the airspace over its western half\" and \"suspending all civil flight permits in the western sector.\" Credible reporting treats this as a regional closure.\n\nThe defendant's strongest point is that the NOTAM is categorized as \"AD Airport Operations\" rather than explicitly an airspace/overflight ban. But the market rule does not require an explicit overflight prohibition — it covers \"commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from\" a major region. Closing all airports in a region with only narrow exceptions directly impacts arrivals and departures across that region. The rule's own cited qualifying example (April 2024 western airspace closure) was described similarly.\n\nUnder **preponderance of the evidence** — more likely than not — the record establishes that Iran broadly closed airport operations across the western Tehran FIR, a major Iranian airspace region, with only limited CAA-controlled daylight exceptions, for non-weather reasons, effective through the deadline. This fits the major-region path.\n\nI'm ready to vote."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_015E4pR9TpQneE6Qj5tRoCYE","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted NOTAMs (A1010/26 and A1015/26) prove Iran's CAA closed ALL airports in the west part of Tehran FIR—a major Iranian airspace region—with only enumerated daylight/CAA-approved exceptions, for non-weather reasons, effective through the May 24 ET deadline. The rule expressly allows limited exceptions including CAA pre-approved flights, and its own qualifying examples include the comparable April 2024 western-airspace closure. Under preponderance, this constitutes a broad closure of commercial flights in a major Iranian airspace region within the market rule's definition.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"anthropic/claude-opus-4.6-fast","usage":{"input":2093,"output":1045,"cacheRead":23800,"cacheWrite":10298,"totalTokens":37236,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781914216015,"responseId":"gen-1781914216-MAWn8sj9Ssz0ChTPkjX0","responseModel":"anthropic/claude-4.6-opus-fast-20260407"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_015E4pR9TpQneE6Qj5tRoCYE","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260619235218\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 850004\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260619235218\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-20T00:24:37.848576192Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":850004,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260619235218\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 850004\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260619235218\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-20T00:24:37.848576192Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":850004,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex11a-20260619235218","member_id":"C4","ok":true,"result":{"text":"Council vote accepted."},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":true,"deadline":"2026-06-20T00:24:37.848576192Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C4","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C4","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":850004,"role_id":"council","turn_number":12}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"submit_council_vote"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781914227845},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"My vote has been accepted. \n\n**Vote: demonstrated**\n\nAs council member C4, I voted that the proposition is **demonstrated**. The admitted record — particularly the raw NOTAMs A1010/26 and A1015/26 issued by Iran's CAA — establishes by a preponderance that Iran initiated a non-weather broad closure of all airports in the west part of Tehran FIR (a major Iranian airspace region), with only limited daylight and CAA-approved exceptions, effective through the May 24 ET deadline. This satisfies the market rule's major-region closure path, consistent with the rule's own qualifying example of the April 2024 western airspace closure and its express tolerance for CAA pre-approved flight exceptions."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"anthropic/claude-opus-4.6-fast","usage":{"input":423,"output":167,"cacheRead":34098,"cacheWrite":2918,"totalTokens":37606,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781914227846,"responseId":"gen-1781914228-415YMZTBwfBMFZGjtQJ4","responseModel":"anthropic/claude-4.6-opus-fast-20260407"}],"willRetry":false}
